<p>Torrential rains between October 6 and 9 triggered floods and landslides across at least five Mexican states, leaving at least 64 people dead and 65 missing, authorities said on Monday [elpais.com#10][france24.com#11][nytimes.com#8][straitstimes.com#1][aljazeera.com#6][abcnews.go.com#9]. The majority of the deaths were reported in Veracruz and Hidalgo, with casualties also in Puebla and other states [aljazeera.com#6][elpais.com#10][nytimes.com#8]. Mexico has deployed about 10,000 troops alongside civilian teams, and helicopters are ferrying food and water to some 200 communities that remain cut off by road [npr.org#3][france24.com#11]. The downpours, linked to a tropical depression, also caused power cuts and blocked roads, hampering access as search operations expand [straitstimes.com#1][japantoday.com#4][aljazeera.com#6][npr.org#3].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/1Ow3vAQBsh-umPklsayk8AxsPlh5Ycb1LgvvF1Kpd3TA7uxxV4Rje1y6VFhqMrmCEUdXsqABnUOrCZT0julXE3WGqiRiXMWRz4P47Y5bRC7UpRJOM6jAN8jbR4ZjvkFQ4HSSaS6tHQo4Ik8CAu9uOaj_xh-FOAaxS_i8SB7uqungrWe3dGb1IEMWO8pz_RhwFMOwRw' alt='A marine helping a woman cross a flooded street on Sunday in Poza Rica, Veracruz, Mexico.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Rescue effort: Mexico has deployed roughly 10,000 troops and used helicopters to deliver food and water to about 200 cut-off communities as search operations widen [npr.org#3][france24.com#11].</li><li>Hardest-hit areas: Casualties span five states, with the majority of deaths in Veracruz and Hidalgo and additional impacts in Puebla [aljazeera.com#6][elpais.com#10][nytimes.com#8].</li><li>Infrastructure damage: The deluge triggered landslides and power cuts, severing ground access to dozens of small communities [japantoday.com#4][firstpost.com#7].</li><li>Weather trigger: A tropical depression over the Gulf Coast and central states fueled the torrential rains that caused the flooding and landslides [straitstimes.com#1].</li><li>Community response: Residents have been clearing paths themselves to enable deliveries of food and supplies to inaccessible towns [firstpost.com#7].</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Mexican government: Officials say thousands of troops are deployed and efforts focus on reaching isolated communities and supporting ongoing search and rescue. (<a href='https://www.france24.com/en/americas/20251014-death-toll-from-mexico-floods-rises-to-64-as-search-operation-expands'>France 24</a>)</li><li>Local residents: Neighbors are working to clear blocked paths so food and supplies can get through to cut-off areas. (<a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/64-dead-in-mexico-as-floods-wreak-havoc-10000-troops-deployed-for-rescue-ops-13941802.html'>Firstpost</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/Heavy-rains-flood-Mexico-towns-leave-nearly-130-dead-or-missing'>Heavy rains flood Mexico towns, leave nearly 130 dead or missing</a> - straitstimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.npr.org/2025/10/14/g-s1-93322/death-toll-torrential-rains-mexico'>Death toll from torrential rains in Mexico rises to 64 as search expands</a> - npr.org</li><li><a href='https://japantoday.com/category/world/torrential-rains-flooding-leave-at-least-64-dead-65-missing-in-mexico1'>Torrential rains, flooding leave at least 64 dead, 65 missing in Mexico</a> - japantoday.com</li><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/gallery/2025/10/14/death-toll-from-devastating-mexico-flooding-rises'>Death toll from devastating Mexico flooding rises</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/64-dead-in-mexico-as-floods-wreak-havoc-10000-troops-deployed-for-rescue-ops-13941802.html'>64 dead in Mexico as floods wreak havoc, 10,000 troops deployed for rescue ops</a> - firstpost.com</li><li><a href='https://www.nytimes.com/2025/10/13/world/americas/mexico-torrential-rain-deaths.html'>Dozens Are Dead and Dozens More Missing as Catastrophic Rains Devastate Mexico</a> - nytimes.com</li><li><a href='http